      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_003/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "ChAMP is an integrated analysis pipeline published in 2014 (Morris et al., 2014), which includes functions for filtering low-quality probes, adjustment for Infinium I and Infinium II probe design, batch effect correction, detecting differentially methylated positions (DMPs), finding differentially methylated regions (DMRs) and detection of copy number aberrations (CNA). The new version of ChAMP, extends and improves this analysis pipeline, adding novel and enhanced functionalities, including detection of differentially methylated genomic blocks (DMB), gene set enrichment analysis (GSEA), a method for correcting cell-type heterogeneity and detection of differentially methylated gene modules.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms ChAMP has DMR detection functionality and mentions Bumphunter as one option for DMR detection, but does not specify application to 'EPIC simulation dataset' or provide expected DMR counts. The specific dataset and quantitative outcome are not mentioned in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1093-bioinformatics-btx513",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When champ.DMR() is applied to the EPIC simulation dataset using bumphunter-based detection, how many differentially methylated regions are identified?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:24:31.515858+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_003/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For supervised analysis, besides limma-based DMP and ProbeLasso-based DMR analysis functions (Butcher and Beck, 2015), there is now added functionality for DMR detection using Bumphunter (Jaffe et al., 2012) and DMRcate (Peters et al., 2015).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms DMR detection capability but does not explicitly describe the structure or contents of output tables (genomic coordinates, statistical metrics).",
