    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/450k-array-data-processing/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "ChAMP loads data from IDAT files using it's novel loading function, or though minfi loading function (Aryee et al., 2014). Probes can be filtered based on detection P-values, chromosomal location, presence of single nucleotide polymorphisms in the probe sequence (Zhou et al., 2016) and cross-hybridization. For normalization, functional normalization (Fortin et al., 2014) has been added as an option alongside beta-mixture quantile normalization (Teschendorff et al., 2013). Singular value decomposition is used to correlate principal components to biological and technical factors, helping the user decide if there are batch effects or confounding factors that need to be adjusted for. For supervised analysis, besides limma-based DMP and ProbeLasso-based DMR analysis functions (Butcher and Beck, 2015), there is now added functionality for DMR detection using Bumphunter (Jaffe et al., 2012) and DMRcate (Peters et al., 2015).",
      "asbval:note": "All claimed functions are explicitly described in the paper: data import, filtering, normalization, batch effect analysis/correction, and differential methylation detection.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1093-bioinformatics-btx513",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "450k-array-data-processing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools[ChAMP].role",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Primary pipeline for data import, filtering, normalization, batch effect analysis and correction, type-2 probe correction, and differential methylation detection on 450k arrays",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:26:27.960541+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/450k-array-data-processing/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "ChAMP loads data from IDAT files using it's novel loading function, or though minfi loading function (Aryee et al., 2014). For normalization, functional normalization (Fortin et al., 2014) has been added as an option alongside beta-mixture quantile normalization (Teschendorff et al., 2013).",
      "asbval:note": "minfi is confirmed as a loading function integrated into ChAMP, and functional normalization is mentioned as an option in ChAMP. However, the paper does not explicitly state that minfi provides functional normalization or that minfi is the source of this normalization method in ChAMP\u2014only that both are available options.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1093-bioinformatics-btx513",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "450k-array-data-processing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools[minfi].role",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Alternative/complementary package offering functional normalization and other 450k analysis methods integrated into ChAMP",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:26:27.960541+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/450k-array-data-processing/007",
