    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/dmr-detection-bumphunter/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "ChAMP loads data from IDAT files using it's novel loading function, or though minfi loading function (Aryee et al., 2014). [...] For normalization, functional normalization (Fortin et al., 2014) has been added as an option alongside beta-mixture quantile normalization (Teschendorff et al., 2013).",
      "asbval:note": "minfi is mentioned for data loading, and functional normalization is available in ChAMP, but the paper does not explicitly attribute functional normalization to minfi\u2014it cites Fortin et al. 2014 as the source. minfi is used for loading, not explicitly for providing the normalization method.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1093-bioinformatics-btx513",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
