    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/illumina-array-data-processing-epic/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "ChAMP loads data from IDAT files using it's novel loading function, or though minfi loading function... For normalization, functional normalization (Fortin et al., 2014) has been added as an option alongside beta-mixture quantile normalization... For supervised analysis, besides limma-based DMP and ProbeLasso-based DMR analysis functions... there is now added functionality for DMR detection using Bumphunter (Jaffe et al., 2012) and DMRcate (Peters et al., 2015).",
      "asbval:note": "All major components of the research question are explicitly covered in the paper's description of ChAMP functionality.",
