    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/interactive-visualization-interpretation-methylation-results/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "ChAMP loads data from IDAT files using it's novel loading function, or though minfi loading function (Aryee et al., 2014)... For normalization, functional normalization (Fortin et al., 2014) has been added as an option alongside beta-mixture quantile normalization (Teschendorff et al., 2013).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms minfi loading function integration and functional normalization availability, but does not explicitly describe minfi as an 'alternative package' for cross-validation. The role is partially supported\u2014minfi is used for data loading and functional normalization is available, but the 'parallel cross-validation' aspect is not mentioned in passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1093-bioinformatics-btx513",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "interactive-visualization-interpretation-methylation-results",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
