    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/random-matrix-theory-application/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "ChAMP loads data from IDAT files using it's novel loading function, or though minfi loading function (Aryee et al., 2014). ... For normalization, functional normalization (Fortin et al., 2014) has been added as an option alongside beta-mixture quantile normalization",
      "asbval:note": "minfi is mentioned as an alternative data loading function, and functional normalization is available in ChAMP itself. The paper does not explicitly describe minfi as providing functional normalization preprocessing before SVD; rather, ChAMP integrates both minfi loading and functional normalization as internal options.",
